cell("markdown","---\n## Phase 1 — Algorithm Construction\n\n### Step 1: Dijkstra's Core Algorithm\nWrite `dijkstra(graph, start)`. The `graph` will be a dictionary like `{'A': {'B': 5, 'C': 2}}`.\nReturn two dictionaries: `distances` and `previous`."),
cell("code","def dijkstra(graph, start):\n    distances = {node: float('inf') for node in graph}\n    distances[start] = 0\n    previous = {node: None for node in graph}\n    \n    # Priority Queue: stores tuples of (distance, node)\n    pq = [(0, start)]\n    \n    while pq:\n        # 1. Pop the node with the smallest distance\n        # current_dist, current_node = heapq.heappop(pq)\n        \n        # 2. Ignore if we already found a better path earlier in the queue\n        # if current_dist > distances[current_node]: continue\n        \n        # 3. Check all neighbors\n        # for neighbor, weight in graph[current_node].items():\n        #     distance = current_dist + weight\n        #     If distance < distances[neighbor]:\n        #         Update distances[neighbor]\n        #         Update previous[neighbor]\n        #         Push (distance, neighbor) to pq\n        \n        # YOUR CODE HERE\n        pass\n        \n    return distances, previous"),
